<font color="#FF0000">ANOTHER RESPONSE TO R. REED</font><br>
<tt>Wed Jun 18  0:59:30 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
R.Reed,<br>
     Part of McNamara's problem is that he was NOT a politician, and knew too little of people.  To bring up Sam Rayburn's famous remark about Kennedy's brainy appointees: &quot;I just wish some of them had run for sheriff at least once.&quot;  The man knew figures, stats and reports, but was out of his league in judging what was going on in Vietnam.  At the time, I believe he was too proud in his learned ignorance to admit that even to himself.
<p><code>-- gerald_ney@icpphil.navy.mil  (Gerald Ney, &quot;professor&quot;, 7/68-7/69) </code><p>


